USERNAME

This program is used to print out the username of the current (or specified)
user.

Synopsis:

$ username [<userspec(s)>] [-q] [-o <opt(s)>] [-pm <pm>] [-V]

where:

<userspec(s)>	optional username, groupspec, or realname to process
-q		to not actually print the username (only provide exit-code)
-o <opt(s)>	option(s): realname, name, pcsname, fullname
-pm <pm>	program-mode <pm>
-V		print program version to the standard-error and then exit

